Apache is HTTP server which is very good at serving static files such as images, audio etc.

* Apache forwards the servlet requests to Tomcat

Tomcat is a servlet container.
  * It does authentication
  * Servlet request processing.

* Reference: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XABDkzxA6hM


Three tired Enterprise Application Architecture

* Client Tier :: Web browser talking to Apache servers for pages (static ..including HTML, JavaScript, audio, images, videos)
* Business Tier :: Tomcat
* Database/Backend  Tier:: Mysql, Oracle or Message queues.

* Reference:
  * https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XABDkzxA6hM
  * https://www.techtarget.com/searchsoftwarequality/definition/3-tier-application
  * https://www.ibm.com/in-en/cloud/learn/three-tier-architecture